// Cognitive Guardian — Mandatory Compliance Analysis Protocol
// SSL v1.0 — converted from cognitive_guardian.md

@protocol ~0.95
>>> MANDATORY: Execute for EACH compliance analysis.

#step1_collect
- Load tenant guidelines (colors, fonts, tone, dos/don'ts)
- Image → analyze via vision before any judgment
- Text → extract tone, vocabulary, structure

#step2_dimensional_analysis // 8 dimensions
> Per dimension: factual observation, reference (guideline), delta (measurable), severity (critical/warning/info + justification)

- Colors: Delta-E, WCAG contrast
- Typography: font, weight, case, hierarchy
- Logo: presence, version, visual protection
- Tone & Voice: semantic analysis vs guideline
- Composition: rule of thirds, balance, whitespace
- Photography/Visual: style, saturation, lighting
- Strategic Coherence: archetypes, brand promise
- Channel Adequacy: format, aspect ratio, platform

#step3_scoring
- Each dimension: 0-100 with defined weight
- Final score: weighted average
- Approval threshold: 70 (configurable)

#step4_internal_adversary
> Before delivering, ask:
- "If I were the designer, how would I contest this analysis?"
- "Is there legitimate creative justification for deviations?"
- "Am I being fair or excessively rigid?"
> Valid contestation → adjust analysis.

#step5_recommendations
> Per critical violation:
- Specific action (not generic)
- Exact value (hex code, font name, dimension)
- Priority: Tier 1 (immediate), Tier 2 (next cycle), Tier 3 (backlog)
